
Upgrading AMP

Upgrading AMP is easy.  You should perform these steps on a running system.  There should be in impact to service.


If upgrading from the AMP-version.tar.gz download from sourceforge:

- save the AMP-version.tar.gz to /usr/src/
- cd /usr/src/ :: change to your /usr/src directory
- rm -rf AMP :: remove your current AMP directory
- tar -zxvf AMP-version.tar.gz :: extract the new AMP tar
- cd AMP :: change to the AMP directory
- ./upgrade.sh :: run the upgrade script



If upgrading AMP from CVS:

- cd /usr/src/ :: change to your /usr/src directory
- rm -rf AMP :: remove your current AMP directory
- cvs -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/amportal login [null password]
- cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/amportal co AMP
- cd AMP :: change to the AMP directory
- ./upgrade.sh :: run the upgrade script


